<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1996-10-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Long-term humoral immunity against viruses: revisiting the issue of plasma cell longevity</TITLE><BODY>Despite extensive documentation of prolonged antibody responses following vaccination or acute viral infection, the mechanisms behind long-term antibody production are not fully understood. We propose the hypothesis that long-lived plasma cells are an important, yet largely overlooked, component of long-term humoral immunity.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>